---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CardGrid from "../../components/CardGrid.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Cookbook" section="cookbook">
  <h1>Cookbook</h1>
  <p>
    This section is a companion to the <a href="https://github.com/pixano/pixano-cookbook">Pixano Cookbook</a> repository.
    Each chapter takes a well-known computer vision benchmark, explains the problem it addresses,
    shows how its data structure maps to Pixano's data model, and walks you through the import and
    annotation workflow. Along the way, you will discover the Pixano features that are most relevant
    to each task.
  </p>

  <CardGrid>
    <Card title="Object Detection" href="/cookbook/object_detection/" icon="target">
      Learn how Pascal VOC maps to Pixano's data model. Import images, annotate with bounding boxes, and explore interactive segmentation.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Video Object Tracking" href="/cookbook/video_tracking/" icon="video">
      Learn how DAVIS maps to Pixano's video model. Understand tracklets, per-frame masks, and temporal annotation workflows.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Multi-View Detection" href="/cookbook/multi_view_detection/" icon="layers">
      Import FLIR ADAS v2 in image or video mode, and browse synchronized RGB + thermal views side by side.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Visual Question Answering" href="/cookbook/vqa/" icon="message">
      Learn how VQAv2 maps to Pixano's data model. Combine Q&A annotation with spatial entity annotation in the same workspace.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Entity Linking" href="/cookbook/entity_linking/" icon="link">
      Import the MEL dataset, link image regions to text spans, and annotate with bounding boxes and text selection.
    </Card>
  </CardGrid>
</DocsLayout>
